cs.NI, cs.DC, cs.SY, cs.DS, cs.AI 

Reasoning: 
1. cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture) - The paper focuses on the efficient deployment of cloudlets in wireless metropolitan area networks to minimize the average access delay of mobile users. This falls under the domain of networking and internet architecture. 
2. cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing) - The paper deals with the placement of cloudlets in a distributed environment to optimize the deployment cost. This falls under the domain of distributed computing. 
3. cs.SY (Systems and Control) - The paper proposes algorithms to optimize the placement of cloudlets to meet the quality of service requirements of mobile users. This falls under the domain of systems and control. 
4. cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) - The paper proposes heuristic and clustering algorithms to solve the cloudlet placement problem. This falls under the domain of data structures and algorithms. 
5. cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) - The paper proposes an integer linear programming formulation to minimize the number of used cloudlets. This falls under the domain of artificial intelligence.
